org.jtrim2.swing.component

Class RenderingResult<ResultType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jtrim2.swing.component.RenderingResult<ResultType>
  • Type Parameters:
    ResultType - the type of the object attached to the rendering

    public final class RenderingResult<ResultType>
extends Object
    Defines the result of a rendering done by an ImageRenderer. The ImageRender must specify if it did a significant, insignificant or no rendering at all and may also attach a user defined object to the rendering it did.

    To create instances of this class, you should use one of the factory methods if possible: noRendering(), insignificant(ResultType) and significant(ResultType).

    Thread safety

    Methods of this class are safe to be accessed from multiple threads concurrently. Also instances of RenderingResult are immutable assuming that the attached object is also immutable.

    Synchronization transparency

    Methods of this class are synchronization transparent.
    See Also:
    ImageRenderer, AsyncRenderingComponent

    • Constructor Detail

      • RenderingResult

        public RenderingResult(RenderingType type,
                       ResultType result)
        Creates a new RenderingResult with the given properties.

        Consider using one of the factory methods instead of calling this constructor:

        • noRendering()
        • insignificant(ResultType)
        • significant(ResultType)
        Parameters:
        type - the RenderingType which is to be returned by the getType() method. This argument cannot be null.
        result - the object to be returned by the getResult() method. This argument is allowed to be null but when type is RenderingType.NO_RENDERING, this argument must be null because you may only return a user defined object if there was any rendering.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - thrown if the specified RenderingType is null
        IllegalArgumentException - thrown if result is not null but the type is RenderingType.NO_RENDERING

    • Method Detail

      • noRendering

        public static <ResultType> RenderingResult<ResultType> noRendering()
        Returns a RenderingResult which has no attached object and whose getType() method returns RenderingType.NO_RENDERING.

        The returned result means that no rendering was done that should be displayed.

        Type Parameters:
        ResultType - the type of the attached result. Although no object is attached to the returned result, this type argument might be needed for type safety.
        Returns:
        a RenderingResult which means that no rendering was done that should be displayed. This method never returns null.

      • insignificant

        public static <ResultType> RenderingResult<ResultType> insignificant(ResultType result)
        Returns a RenderingResult with the specified attached object and whose getType() method returns RenderingType.INSIGNIFICANT_RENDERING.

        The returned result means that the rendering done should be displayed but is not significant. That is, insignificant renderings are renderings which in itself does not contain the main interest of the user looking at the rendered image.

        Type Parameters:
        ResultType - the type of the attached object
        Parameters:
        result - the object attached to the rendering. This argument is allowed to be null.
        Returns:
        a RenderingResult signaling that an insignificant rendering was done. This method never returns null.

      • significant

        public static <ResultType> RenderingResult<ResultType> significant(ResultType result)
        Returns a RenderingResult with the specified attached object and whose getType() method returns RenderingType.SIGNIFICANT_RENDERING.

        The returned result means that the rendering done should be displayed and is not significant. That is, significant renderings are renderings containing the main interest of the user.

        Type Parameters:
        ResultType - the type of the attached object
        Parameters:
        result - the object attached to the rendering. This argument is allowed to be null.
        Returns:
        a RenderingResult signaling that a significant rendering was done. This method never returns null.

      • getType

        public RenderingType getType()
        Returns if there was any rendering done and if there was, it was significant or not.

        If this method returns RenderingType.NO_RENDERING, getResult() will always return null.

        Returns:
        the RenderingType determining if there was any rendering done and if there was, it was significant or not. This method never returns null.

      • getResult

        public ResultType getResult()
        Returns the object attached to the rendering. The meaning of this object depends on the renderer.
        Returns:
        the object attached to the rendering. This method may return null, if null was specified at construction time.

      • hasRendered

        public boolean hasRendered()
        Returns true if the renderer did some rendering.

        This method call is equivalent to: getType() != RenderingType.NO_RENDERING.

        Returns:
        true if the renderer did some rendering, false otherwise

      • isSignificant

        public boolean isSignificant()
        Returns true if the renderer did some rendering and it was significant.

        This method call is equivalent to: getType() == RenderingType.SIGNIFICANT_RENDERING.

        Returns:
        true if the renderer did some rendering and it was significant, false otherwise
